# React & Next.js Performance Rules

Prioritized performance optimization guide from [Vercel Engineering](https://github.com/vercel-labs/agent-skills/tree/main/skills/react-best-practices). Apply these rules when writing, reviewing, or refactoring React/Next.js code.

## Priority 1: Eliminating Waterfalls (CRITICAL)

### Use `Promise.all()` for independent async operations

```typescript
// BAD: sequential — 3 round trips
const user = await fetchUser()
const posts = await fetchPosts()
const comments = await fetchComments()

// GOOD: parallel — 1 round trip
const [user, posts, comments] = await Promise.all([
  fetchUser(), fetchPosts(), fetchComments()
])
```

### Defer `await` until actually needed

```typescript
// BAD: blocks both branches
async function handle(userId: string, skip: boolean) {
  const data = await fetchData(userId)
  if (skip) return { skipped: true }
  return process(data)
}

// GOOD: only awaits when needed
async function handle(userId: string, skip: boolean) {
  if (skip) return { skipped: true }
  const data = await fetchData(userId)
  return process(data)
}
```

### Start promises early, await late in API routes

```typescript
// GOOD
export async function GET() {
  const sessionPromise = auth()
  const configPromise = fetchConfig()
  const session = await sessionPromise
  const [config, data] = await Promise.all([
    configPromise, fetchData(session.user.id)
  ])
  return Response.json({ data, config })
}
```

### Use Suspense boundaries to stream content

```tsx
// GOOD: layout renders immediately, data streams in
function Page() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Header />
      <Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
        <DataDisplay />
      </Suspense>
      <Footer />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Priority 2: Bundle Size (CRITICAL)

### Dynamic imports for heavy components

```tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic'
const HeavyComponent = dynamic(() => import('./heavy').then(m => m.Heavy), { ssr: false })
```

### Avoid barrel file imports — import directly

```tsx
// BAD
import { Button } from '@/components'
// GOOD
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
```

### Defer non-critical third-party libraries

```tsx
const Analytics = dynamic(
  () => import('@vercel/analytics/react').then(m => m.Analytics),
  { ssr: false }
)
```

## Priority 3: Server-Side Performance (HIGH)

### Authenticate Server Actions like API routes

Server Actions are public endpoints. Always verify auth inside each action.

```typescript
'use server'
export async function deleteUser(userId: string) {
  const session = await getSession()
  if (!session) throw new Error('Unauthorized')
  if (session.user.id !== userId && session.user.role !== 'admin') {
    throw new Error('Forbidden')
  }
  await db.delete(users).where(eq(users.id, userId))
}
```

### Minimize data at RSC boundaries

Only pass the fields client components actually use.

```tsx
// BAD: serializes all 50 fields
<Profile user={user} />

// GOOD: serializes only what's needed
<Profile name={user.name} avatarUrl={user.avatarUrl} />
```

### Parallel data fetching via component composition

```tsx
// GOOD: Header and Sidebar fetch simultaneously
function Page() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Header />   {/* async, fetches independently */}
      <Sidebar />  {/* async, fetches independently */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Use `React.cache()` for per-request dedup

```typescript
import { cache } from 'react'
export const getCurrentUser = cache(async () => {
  const session = await auth()
  if (!session?.user?.id) return null
  return getUserById(db, session.user.id)
})
```

### Use `after()` for non-blocking operations

```typescript
import { after } from 'next/server'
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  await updateDatabase(request)
  after(async () => { await logAction(request) })
  return Response.json({ status: 'success' })
}
```

## Priority 4: Re-render Optimization (MEDIUM)

### Derive state during render — don't store in useState + useEffect

```tsx
// BAD
const [fullName, setFullName] = useState('')
useEffect(() => setFullName(first + ' ' + last), [first, last])

// GOOD
const fullName = first + ' ' + last
```

### Don't define components inside components

Causes remount on every render, destroying state and DOM.

### Use functional `setState` for stable callbacks

```tsx
// GOOD: no stale closures, stable reference
const addItem = useCallback((item: Item) => {
  setItems(curr => [...curr, item])
}, [])
```

### Use lazy state initialization for expensive values

```tsx
// GOOD: runs only once
const [data, setData] = useState(() => expensiveComputation())
```

### Use `useDeferredValue` / `startTransition` for non-urgent updates

### Don't wrap simple primitive expressions in `useMemo`

### Narrow effect dependencies to primitives

```tsx
// BAD: re-runs on any user field change
useEffect(() => { console.log(user.id) }, [user])
// GOOD: re-runs only when id changes
useEffect(() => { console.log(user.id) }, [user.id])
```

## Priority 5: Rendering Performance (MEDIUM)

### Use `content-visibility: auto` for long lists

```css
.list-item { content-visibility: auto; contain-intrinsic-size: 0 80px; }
```

### Hoist static JSX outside components

### Animate div wrapper around SVG, not SVG directly (hardware acceleration)

### Use `suppressHydrationWarning` only for expected mismatches (dates, locale)

### Use ternary `? :` not `&&` for conditional rendering (prevents rendering `0`)

### Use `next/script` with `strategy` prop instead of raw script tags

### Use React DOM resource hints (`preconnect`, `preload`, `prefetchDNS`)

## Priority 6: JavaScript Performance (LOW-MEDIUM)

### Build `Map`/`Set` for repeated lookups (O(1) vs O(n))

### Use `toSorted()` not `sort()` (immutability in React)

### Use `flatMap` to map + filter in one pass

### Early return from functions

### Cache property access in hot loops

### Avoid layout thrashing — batch DOM writes, then read

